<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 15 at 4:45PM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...Periods of mixed precipitation including spotty freezing
rain expected this evening...
Light mixed precipitation is occurring in western Mohawk Valley,
southern Adirondacks, Lake George and northern Saratoga area. A
light dusting of snow and sleet is possible along with isolated
pockets of light freezing rain as temperatures hover around
freezing.
Temperatures are expected to rise into the mid and upper 30s
through the night, changing all light mixed precipitation to
rain. Motorists are advised to use caution, slow down and allow
for extra space between yourself and other motorists through this
evening.</description>
